title: leaking upcoming
extract: A leak involves the release of something. It can be a behind-someone's-back leak of sensitive information, a leak from a milk carton, or a leak in the roof that lets rain water drip in. As a verb, leak means to allow light or fluid to escape, or to enter or escape as though through a hole.
